This is my recipe for a nice and healthy cupcakes

Ingredients:

1 cup whole wheat flour
1/2 cup rolled oats
1 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp salt
2 ripe bananas, mashed
1/4 cup honey or maple syrup
1/4 cup unsweetened applesauce
1/4 cup Greek yogurt
1 egg
1 tsp vanilla extract
Optional:

Dark chocolate chips
Chopped nuts
Dried fruits
Shredded coconut

How:

Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a muffin tin with cupcake liners.
In a large bowl, combine the whole wheat flour, rolled oats, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
In another bowl, mix the mashed bananas, honey or maple syrup, applesauce, Greek yogurt, egg, and vanilla extract until well combined.
Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix until just combined.
Optional: Fold in dark chocolate chips, chopped nuts, dried fruits, or shredded coconut.
Divide the batter evenly among the cupcake liners.
Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Serving:
Let the cupcakes cool completely before serving. Enjoy as a healthy snack or dessert!

That's all :) Enjoy your healthy cupcakes!
